{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897702587,"sessionID":"ses_28442396fffeYAYu7CLqKnJbSn","part":{"id":"prt_d7bbddc0b001EKylbcfB3R7VZX","messageID":"msg_d7bbdc76e001Me5MsrBAHMguo7","sessionID":"ses_28442396fffeYAYu7CLqKnJbSn","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_b729d218a25a4254ab646607","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The overall project structure and architecture\n2. Any existing spec files (look for *.spec.md, delta-spec.md, specs/, docs/ directories)\n3. Any existing OpenSpec format examples in the project\n4. The current state of any documentation framework\n5. Package.json or similar config files to understand the tech stack\n\nSearch for patterns like:\n- **/*spec*.md\n- **/delta-spec.md\n- **/specs/**\n- **/openspec/**\n- **/docs/**\n- package.json files\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- Any existing spec formats found (show examples if found)\n- Current documentation setup\n- Tech stack details\n- Any relevant configuration files","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_284420c39ffegndP6Cs3x2tDOj (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the AgentCube project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive AgentCube Project Analysis\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── .github/workflows/          # 12 CI/CD workflow files\n├── bin/                        # Build output directory\n├── changes/                    # 42 AR (Agent Request) change directories (AR-001 through AR-042)\n│   └── AR-NNN/\n│       ├── delta-spec.md       # Delta specification (requirements in Gherkin-like format)\n│       ├── design.md           # Technical design document\n│       ├── proposal.md         # Feature proposal\n│       └── tasks.md            # Task breakdown with dependency graphs\n├── ci-cd/                      # CI/CD spec + design\n├── cli-toolkit/                # CLI spec + design\n├── client-go/                  # Generated Kubernetes client library\n├── cmd/                        # Go binary entrypoints\n│   ├── agentd/\n│   ├── cli/                    # Python CLI (kubectl-agentcube)\n│   ├── picod/\n│   ├── router/\n│   └── workloadmanager/\n├── code-execution/             # Code execution spec + design\n├── deployment/                 # Deployment spec + design\n├── docker/                     # Dockerfiles (Dockerfile, Dockerfile.router, Dockerfile.picod)\n├── example/                    # Example apps (pcap-analyzer)\n├── hack/                       # Code generation scripts\n├── idle-cleanup/               # Idle cleanup spec + design\n├── integrations/               # Dify plugin integration spec + design\n├── manifests/charts/base/      # Helm chart (templates, CRDs, values.yaml)\n├── pkg/                        # Go packages\n│   ├── agentd/\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/  # CRD type definitions\n│   ├── common/\n│   ├── picod/\n│   ├── router/\n│   ├── store/\n│   └── workloadmanager/\n├── python-sdk/                 # Python SDK (agentcube package)\n├── sandbox-orchestration/      # Sandbox orchestration spec + design\n├── session-routing/            # Session routing spec + design\n├── session-store/              # Session store spec + design\n├── test/                       # Test infrastructure (e2e)\n├── testing/                    # Additional test utilities\n├── delta-spec.md               # Root-level delta spec (AR-038: Go unit tests)\n├── design.md                   # Root-level design doc (AR-040: Python SDK tests)\n├── go.mod / go.sum             # Go module definition\n├── Makefile                    # Build system\n├── project.md                  # OpenSpec project context\n├── proposal.md                 # Feature proposal (AR-036: Dify integration)\n├── tasks.md                    # Task breakdown (AR-023: CLI invoke/status)\n└── test_spec.md                # TDD specification (test case catalog)\n```\n\n### 2. Existing Spec Formats Found\n\nThe project uses a **multi-layered specification system** with three primary formats:\n\n#### Format A: Module-level `spec.md` files\nLocated at the root of each feature module. Uses **Gherkin-style Given/When/Then** scenarios with **SHALL/SHOULD/MAY** normative language.\n\n**Example** (`session-store/spec.md`):\n```markdown\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey\nproviders with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, ...\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n```\n\nFound at 10 locations:\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md`\n\n#### Format B: Change-level `delta-spec.md` files\nLocated inside each `changes/AR-NNN/` directory. These are **incremental specs** describing what a specific change request adds/modifies/deletes. The root-level `delta-spec.md` (AR-038) is the most elaborate at 826 lines, using a structured format with:\n\n- **R-N: Section headers** for requirement groups\n- **Requirement: Name** for individual requirements\n- **Scenario: Description** with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN blocks\n- **File Structure** table mapping new test files to their roles\n- **Dependencies** table listing required libraries\n\n**Example** (`changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md`):\n```markdown\n# AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition -- Delta Spec\n\n## Purpose\nDefine the Go type system for the CodeInterpreter Custom Resource Definition...\n\n## Requirements\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD type definition\nThe system SHALL define CodeInterpreter as a namespaced Kubernetes custom resource...\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type is a valid Kubernetes object\n- **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go file exists\n- **WHEN** the Go compiler processes the package\n- **THEN** CodeInterpreter SHALL embed metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta...\n```\n\nFound at 36 locations:\n- Root: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md`\n- Per-AR: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-{002,003,004,005,006,007,010,011,017-042}/delta-spec.md`\n\n#### Format C: `test_spec.md` (TDD catalog)\nA high-level test case catalog at the root:\n```markdown\n## 1. Core Controller Tests (Workload Manager)\n- **TestCase-WM-001**: Verify Sandbox creation endpoint...\n- **TestCase-WM-002**: Verify Sandbox idempotency...\n```\n\n### 3. OpenSpec Format\n\nThe project explicitly references \"OpenSpec\" in `project.md`:\n```markdown\n# AgentCube -- OpenSpec Project Context\n> Source: github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n```\n\nThe OpenSpec convention used here includes:\n- **AR-NNN** numbering (Agent Request) for change tracking\n- **project.md** as the project context file\n- **proposal.md** for feature proposals with Purpose, Scope, Impact Analysis, Alternatives, Acceptance Criteria, and Status\n- **design.md** for technical implementation details (Architecture, Data Structures, API Contracts, Error Handling, Testing Strategy)\n- **tasks.md** for task breakdown with dependency graphs and parallelizable groups\n- **delta-spec.md** for incremental requirement specs\n\n### 4. Current Documentation Framework\n\nThe documentation follows a **layered, spec-driven approach**:\n\n| Layer | Files | Purpose |\n|-------|-------|---------|\n| Project Context | `project.md` | Tech stack, architecture diagram, conventions |\n| Module Specs | `{module}/spec.md` | Normative requirements for each subsystem |\n| Module Design | `{module}/design.md` | Technical implementation details |\n| Change Proposals | `changes/AR-NNN/proposal.md` | Feature proposals with alternatives analysis |\n| Change Designs | `changes/AR-NNN/design.md` | Per-change technical designs |\n| Change Delta Specs | `changes/AR-NNN/delta-spec.md` | Incremental requirements |\n| Change Tasks | `changes/AR-NNN/tasks.md` | Task breakdown with dependency graphs |\n| Test Catalog | `test_spec.md` | High-level test case requirements |\n\nThere is **no `docs/` directory**, **no `specs/` directory**, and **no `openspec/` directory**. Specs are co-located with their respective modules or in the `changes/` directory.\n\n### 5. Tech Stack Details\n\n#### Go Backend (server-side)\n- **Language:** Go 1.25.0 (module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`)\n- **HTTP Framework:** Gin v1.10.0\n- **Kubernetes:** client-go v0.34.1, controller-runtime v0.22.2, API machinery v0.34.1\n- **CRD API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **Storage:** go-redis/v9 v9.18.0, valkey-go v1.0.73, miniredis v2.37.0 (testing)\n- **Auth:** golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.2 (JWT RS256)\n- **Metrics:** prometheus/client_golang v1.22.0\n- **Testing:** testify v1.11.1\n- **Logging:** klog/v2 v2.130.1, zap v1.27.0\n\n#### Python SDK/CLI\n- **Language:** Python >= 3.9\n- **SDK Package:** `agentcube-sdk` v0.1.0 (setuptools build)\n- **SDK Dependencies:** requests, PyJWT >= 2.0.0, cryptography\n- **CLI Framework:** Typer (with Rich for output formatting)\n- **Linting:** ruff\n- **Testing:** pytest\n\n#### Build & Deployment\n- **Build System:** Makefile with targets for build, test, docker, lint, helm, python\n- **Container Images:** 3 images (agentcube/workloadmanager, router, picod) via multi-stage Docker builds on Alpine 3.19\n- **Packaging:** Helm 3 chart at `manifests/charts/base/`\n- **CI/CD:** GitHub Actions (12 workflows): build, lint, test, coverage, e2e, codegen-check, codespell, copyright, release publishing, workflow approval\n- **Code Generation:** `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 via `make gen-client`\n\n#### Integrations\n- **Dify Plugin:** Python plugin with `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n- **Example App:** PCAP Analyzer using FastAPI + LangChain/LangGraph\n\n#### Go Binary Components (4)\n1. **router** -- Session-aware HTTP proxy to sandbox pods\n2. **workloadmanager** -- Control plane API for sandbox lifecycle\n3. **agentd** -- Idle cleanup controller\n4. **picod** -- Code execution engine daemon\n\n### 6. Key Configuration Files\n\n| File | Path | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Go module | `go.mod` | Module definition, all dependencies |\n| Python package | `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` | SDK build config |\n| Makefile | `Makefile` | Unified build system (Go, Docker, Helm, Python) |\n| Helm values | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default deployment values |\n| Helm chart | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata |\n| CRDs | `manifests/charts/base/crds/` | AgentRuntime + CodeInterpreter CRD YAMLs |\n| Dify manifest | `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Dify plugin descriptor |\n\n### 7. Summary of Spec File Counts\n\n| Pattern | Count |\n|---------|-------|\n| `**/*spec*.md` | 47 files |\n| `**/delta-spec.md` | 36 files (1 root + 35 in changes/) |\n| `**/design.md` | 53 files (1 root + 42 in changes/ + 10 in modules) |\n| `**/spec.md` (module-level) | 10 files |\n| `changes/AR-NNN/` directories | 42 directories (AR-001 through AR-042) |\n| `**/proposal.md` | Multiple (root + per-AR) |\n| `**/tasks.md` | Multiple (root + per-AR) |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_284420c39ffegndP6Cs3x2tDOj","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775897539523,"end":1775897702585}}}}
